In article <2kiej4$qja@cnn.MOTOWN.GE.COM> pbosch@motown.ge.com writes:
>Re the self-executing cipher extractor;
>
>What if I go into the executable and change the comparison such that only 
>an _in_correct answer will kick off the deciphering process?  ...And then
>change the place where the executable validation (checksum, or whatever)
>is formed, such that only a _modified_ executable will be permitted to run?
>
>I've changed two machine-level JNZ instructions to JZ, and ( I think )
>brought the technique to its knees...
>
>Comments?
>

The correct passphrase is required to form the IDEA key.  Decryption
is impossible without this key.

